
** Export Users

  - Do not invoke expdp with SYSDBA

** Roles

  - 'EXPORT FULL DATABASE'
  - 'IMPORT FULL DATABASE'

** Modes

  - schema
  - table
  - tablespace
  - transportable tabelspace

** Directories

  - dir:file
  - directory option
  - environment DATA_PUMP_DIR
  - object DATA_PUMP_DIR, if nothing is specified


  SQL> create directory data_pump_dir as '/O1/oradata/data_pump';
  SQL> grant read, write on directory data_pumb to ops$maierh;

** Versions

  - The version option needs to be specified if the data will be moved
    from a newer database version to a older database version.

** Options

  - attach [=[schema_name.]job_name] See the jobs in
    USER_DATAPUMP_JOBS.

  - dumpfile = [directory_object:]file_name [, ...] Specify the %U
    template with the PARALLEL option.

  - extimate
  - estimate_only=y

  - exclude
  - filesize
  - flashback_scn
  - flashback_time
  - full
  - help
  - include

  - job_name=jobname Default is a system generated job name

  - schemas=schema_name [, ...]
  - status[=seconds]
  - tables
  - version


** Examples

  - $ expdp direcotry=data_pump_dir userid=/
  - exports the schema of the user '/'. The dump file is expdat.dmp.

** Import

** Options

  - remap_datafile
  - remap_schema
  - remap_tablespace
  - reuse_datafiles (possible loss of data)
  - skip_unusable_indexes

  - sqlfile = [directory_object:]file_name

  - table_exists_action = {skip | append | truncate | replace}

  - transform

** NETWORK_LINK

as DBA
  - create directory logs ...
  - create tablespace dbs datafile ...
  - create user dbs identified by ...
  - alter user dbs default tablespace dbs
  - alter user dbs quota 1g on dbs
  - grant write on directory ... to dbs
  - grant read  on directory ... to dbs
  - grant connect, resource to dbs
  - grant create database link to dbs

as USER
  - create databse link ...

  $ impdp userid=dbs/xxx@t1 network_link=hml schemas=dbs \
      logfile=logs:dbs.log remap_tablespace=users:dbs
